name: GAYETIES
description: Syntax crystals come in so many forms, sometimes descending letters that form larger words or sentences made of locked words within other words, or other variations. The word GAYETIES phonetically sounds and looks like gay ties. Would wouldn't want gay ties in their life? The world is a better place because of gay ties. lol Let's look deeper into this rare syntax crystal. What do we see? Oh my lord, it's A GAY YETI and it TIES A TIE! Good for that gay yeti! Looking spiffy for it's fancy, flirtatious, and flamboyant Fire Island night of fun in the middle of February. All the greatest qualities of a gay yeti. You go grrrrrrrl!
